cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.CR

This paper discusses the specification of Service Level Agreements (SLAs) for IoT applications, which involves networking, distributed computing, software engineering, and security aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the need for SLAs to account for the multi-layered nature of IoT applications, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper proposes a conceptual model and a new SLA grammar, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
